HEADWORD: Papillote
<hw>Pap"il*lote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>papillon</ets> a butterfly.]</ety> <def>A small piece of paper on
which women roll up their hair to make it curl; a curl paper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Papillous</ent>⟦br⟧
